---
const TOOLS = [
  { name: "Claude", glyph: "C" },
  { name: "Cursor", glyph: "▶" },
  { name: "ChatGPT", glyph: "○" },
  { name: "Aider", glyph: "A" },
];
---

<section class="section" data-screen-label="Why">
  <div class="why">
    <span class="eyebrow">Built for AI workflows</span>
    <h2>Stop screenshotting → uploading → copying → pasting.</h2>
    <p>
      You're working with Claude Code on a remote VPS. You need to show the
      model a UI bug, a design mockup, a stack trace. The usual workflow
      (screenshot, open browser, upload to imgur, copy the URL, paste) is six
      steps, three apps, and a dozen seconds you'll never get back.
    </p>
    <p>
      Snap2Link collapses it into one keystroke. Uploads to <strong>your</strong>
      Google Drive with the minimum scope possible. No third-party server, no
      account to create, no telemetry. The link is on your clipboard before the
      toast finishes.
    </p>
    <div class="tools-row">
      {
        TOOLS.map((t) => (
          <span class="tool-chip">
            <span class="glyph">{t.glyph}</span>
            {t.name}
          </span>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
